Summary: Rust-colored disk, with a squarish dome.
divs: sighting detailswitness called assistant state director to file her report. witness reported the following: on november 8, 2010, she was riding in a car with a friend. they were driving westbound on sunset blvd. in renton, about two blocks east of i-405. the witness looked off to the left and saw an object that appeared to be resting on top of the trees. she yelled at her friend to look, but the friend did not reply or react in any way. she said that they were actually above the object. as they passed by, the witness could see that the object was above the trees, not in contact with them. she described the object as being approximately 25 to 40 feet in diameter. it was round, but not really disk-shaped. she decribed it as "like a prescription bottle top". round, but with a square top. on top was a smaller protrusion of the same shape. set into that were square or rectangular depressions, the same color as the rest of the object. the object was a dull, rust-brown. the witness said that at the closest, they were about 1\2 to 1 block from the object. when she first saw the object, she was amazed and excited. she said that she looked around, expecting this to be some display at a business, but there were no businesses at that location. after passing by the object, the car turned and she did not see the object again. she does not know if it ever moved. when her friend did not react to neither the object nor the witnesses reaction, the witness did not say anything more about it. the witness said that she never discussed this with the other woman again, and they are no longer friends (this separation is not related to the sighting).
